p: A total of 53 compounds were identified. The highest relative percentages of compounds were the phenylpropanoids ( E)-asarone (22.6% in C1), elemicin (35.9% and 52.7% in C2 and C3, respectively), the sesquiterpenes hydrocarbons bicyclogermacrene (66.7% in M1) and δ-elemene with 32.2% in P1 and 37.9% in P2, as well as the oxygenated sesquiterpene α-bisabolol, with 93.7% in the S region.
